.\" m4.1 - Heirloom Darwin port synthesised man page
.TH M4 1 "2026-07-03" "Heirloom Darwin port" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
m4 \- macro processor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B m4
.RI "[\-e] [\-s] [\-B" int "] [\-H" int "] [\-S" int "] [\-T" int "]"
.br
   [\-D
.IR name [= value ]]...
[\-U
.IR name ]...
[
.I file
...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B m4
is a general-purpose macro processor. It reads its input, expands
built-in and user-defined macros, and writes the result to standard
output.  Input comes from the concatenation of the named
.I file
arguments; if no
.I file
is given, or if a file argument is the single character \-, then
standard input is read.
.PP
Built-in macros include
.BR define ,
.BR undefine ,
.BR ifdef ,
.BR ifelse ,
.BR include ,
.BR sinclude ,
.BR changequote ,
.BR changecom ,
.BR divert ,
.BR undivert ,
.BR divnum ,
.BR dnl ,
.BR eval ,
.BR len ,
.BR index ,
.BR substr ,
.BR translit ,
.BR incr ,
.BR decr ,
.BR syscmd ,
.BR sysval ,
.BR maketemp ,
.BR errprint ,
.BR dumpdef ,
.BR shift ,
.BR pushdef ,
.BR popdef ,
.BR traceon ,
.BR traceoff ,
.BR m4wrap .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-e
Operate interactively: unbuffer output and ignore interrupts.
.TP
.B \-s
Emit line-synchronisation output for the C preprocessor.
.TP
.BI \-B " int"
Change size of the push-back and argument-collection buffers.
.TP
.BI \-D " name" [= value ]
Define
.I name
to
.IR value ,
or empty in the absence of
.IR value .
.TP
.BI \-H " int"
Change size of the symbol-table hash array.
.TP
.BI \-S " int"
Change size of the call stack.
.TP
.BI \-T " int"
Change size of the token buffer.
.TP
.BI \-U " name"
Undefine
.IR name .
.SH HEIRLOOM DARWIN PORT
This binary is the Heirloom port of SVR4
.BR m4 (1).
It supports the shared modality flags added by the port
(\fB\-\-help\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR, \fB\-\-variants\fR,
\fB\-\-describe\-modality\fR, \fB\-\-variant=\fIname\fR,
\fB\-\-dialect=\fIname\fR) as documented in
.BR heirloom-modality (7).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cc (1),
.BR heirloom-modality (7).
.SH HISTORY
.B m4
was introduced by Kernighan and Ritchie in 1977 as a companion to
.BR nroff (1)
and as a stage for portable C preprocessor macros. See the
package's
.B BIBLIOGRAPHY.md
for citations.
